(950, 1, '2019-03-19 04:47:43', '2019-03-19 04:47:43', 'The Second KMAT Kerala Entrance Examination for admission to MBA course for the academic year 2019-20 is proposed to be conducted on June 16, 2019 by Cochin University of Science and Technology (CUSAT) under the supervision of Admission Supervisory Committee (ASC). Aspiring candidates may apply online through the website <a href=\"https://kmatkerala.in\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://kmatkerala.in</a> from 5th march 2019 5.00 PM onwards. The last date for submitting online application is 31.05.2019, 4.00 PM. The application fee prescribed for general candidate is Rs 1000/- and Rs 750/- for SC/ST Candidate.\r\n\r\n<strong>In the discussion held on 05.06.2018 Dr. Chandrasekhar also opined that it is better to postpone the KMAT Kerala entrance examination from June 24th and the same shall be conducted on 08.07.2018. <span class=\"none\">Since the issue is still persisting, it is decided that KMAT Kerala entrance examination scheduled on 24.06.2018 is postponed to 08.07.2018.</span> The below table shows the new time schedule for Entrance Examination on 08.07.2018.\r\nIn the event of postponement of the entrance exam. The date of commencement of Academic Session shall also be shifted to <span class=\"none\">8th August 2018</span> and the last date of closing of admission will be <span class=\"none\">15.08.2018.</span></strong>', 'NOTIFICATIONS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 04:47:43', '2019-03-19 04:47:43', '', 250, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/250-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
