(999, 1, '2019-03-19 10:53:23', '2019-03-19 10:53:23', '<h4>Airline Industry</h4>\r\nKnowledge of various industries, it\'s nature their business models etc. found to be very effective in enhancing the aspirations of young managers. AtVSMS in this series Practicing managers from different industries interact with students and enlight them with the essential details of the respective industry. Mr. Rajive Soman, Manager Revenue of Maldivian Airlines introduced the Airline industry to our MBA students. His session covered Brief History, Essentials of Airline Business, Revenue Management strategies and few case studies on Airline Industries made the session really rich and useful. Thanks to Ms. Ambily for organizing it well.', 'INDUSTRY FAMILIARISATION PROGRAMME', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '277-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 10:53:23', '2019-03-19 10:53:23', '', 277, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/277-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1000, 1, '2019-03-19 11:01:24', '2019-03-19 11:01:24', '<h4>Industry Readiness Training Program by Mr.Emmanuel Braggs</h4>\r\nA 3-day workshop on Industry readiness for the students was conducted in the college to make the students get awareness about the different aspects of the recruitment process &amp; the various levels included in the recruitment. The program incorporated various training\r\nsessions for the students including Mock Interviews. Group Discussions etc. The session\r\nwas handled by Mr.Emmanuel Braggs from Pune. The program was very fruitful for the students with so much learning and also fun-filled through various quiz programs and other activities &amp; games.', 'INDUSTRY INTERACTIONS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '279-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 11:01:24', '2019-03-19 11:01:24', '', 279, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/279-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1001, 1, '2019-03-19 11:15:28', '2019-03-19 11:15:28', 'The Business Quiz happens weekly once which is mainly conducted by the students based on the news from the Business Line of the respective week. The students are divided into various\r\ngroups that compete with each other. The winning group is awarded prizes. Each group is\r\ncoordinated and guided by a faculty.', 'BUSINESS QUIZ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '267-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 11:15:28', '2019-03-19 11:15:28', '', 267, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/267-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1002, 1, '2019-03-19 11:16:27', '2019-03-19 11:16:27', 'The Industry Familiarisation sessions are taken by students based on their own choice of industry. Presentations are conducted by a group of students detailing about the chosen industry. A jury of faculty members will be present for the session and suggestions are provided to the students.', 'INDUSTRY FAMILIARISATION PROGRAMME', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '277-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 11:16:27', '2019-03-19 11:16:27', '', 277, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/277-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1003, 1, '2019-03-19 12:04:17', '2019-03-19 12:04:17', '<ul class=\"list-unstyled list-arw\">\r\n 	<li>Formal Application form for the MBA Admission can be obtained from the VISWAJYOTHI School of Management Studies Office in person on payment of Rs. 500.</li>\r\n 	<li>Application forms may also be downloaded from the link below. Such applications have to be submitted along with a DD of Rs. 500/- in favour of \" Principal, VISWAJYOTHI College of Engineering and Technology\" payable at Vazhakulam, Muvattupuzha.</li>\r\n 	<li>The duly filled application forms along with attested copies of the necessary documents can be submitted directly or by registered post addressing the college so as to reach the college office on or before the prescribed date. Applicants shall obtained acknowledgment from the college for application submitted directly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Application submitted to the college should be completed in all respects. The candidate should fill in all the items in the application form in his / her own handwriting.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"list-arw-sub\">Copies of following Certificates / Documents Attested by Gazetted Officer/Head of the Institution where the student had studied should be submitted along with the application.\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled \">\r\n 	<li>10 / 12 or equivalent certificate in proof of the date of birth.</li>\r\n 	<li>Mark list of the qualifying examination</li>\r\n 	<li>Score card of MAT/C-MAT/KMAT</li>\r\n 	<li>In case of candidates claiming any sort of reservation or special consideration, document to prove such claims must be submitted along with the application.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'APPLY ONLINE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '244-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 12:04:17', '2019-03-19 12:04:17', '', 244, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/244-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1004, 1, '2019-03-19 12:08:56', '2019-03-19 12:08:56', 'Department of Management Studies of VISWAJYOTHI College of Engineering and Technology, popularly known as VISWAJYOTHI School of Management Studies (VSMS) is a part of the VISWAJYOTHI College of Engineering and Technology (VJCET), one of the premier self-financing Engineering Colleges of Kerala, approved by AICTE and affiliated to Kerala Technological University. The College, established in 2001, is managed by the Diocesan Technical Education Trust under the auspices of the Kothamangalam Diocese.', 'HOME', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-19 12:08:56', '2019-03-19 12:08:56', '', 8, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1005, 1, '2019-03-20 04:47:41', '2019-03-20 04:47:41', 'Women\'s Day at VSMS was a memorable learning experience. In its organizing, we learned how to stay positive in turbulent times. How to swing as a group to positive forces. Students you proved you are Managers. Our celebration was a beautiful blend Ms. Anupama Roy and Ms. Anu Sunil 2 successful women Entrepreneurs shared the inspiring Journey of a women Entrepreneur.\n\nLessons they shared are: Follow your passion; Plan every day clearly; Belief in ourselves; Gain hands own experience; Manage your energy; Build great team; Plan for your capital; Learn from the complaint and Be god-fearing:\n\nMs. Zeanath Ashraf a social worker with Mother Theresa Touch shared the transformation of\nGunda Attani Aneesh into a family man and the miserable life of AIDS patients. The audience listened with tears in their eyes. Students honoured the Ammas of our campus who take care of the sanitation of the premises and hospitality of the guests. They acknowledge the value of their contribution. Let\'s keep on doing with everything involvement\nand\nmindfulness.Birthday of Dr Anu George and Ms\nLidhiya made the occasion very warm. Special\nappreciation to Nayana, Franklin, Jojin, Shruthi,\nSreenath Sir and Ambily Miss for the effective\ncoordination.', 'Women\'s Day Celebration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-03-20 04:47:41', '2019-03-20 04:47:41', '', 68, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/68-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1006, 1, '2019-03-20 04:48:24', '2019-03-20 04:48:24', 'Women\'s Day at VSMS was a memorable learning experience. In its organizing, we learned how to stay positive in turbulent times. How to swing as a group to positive forces. Students you proved you are Managers. Our celebration was a beautiful blend Ms. Anupama Roy and Ms. Anu Sunil 2 successful women Entrepreneurs shared the inspiring Journey of a women Entrepreneur.\r\n\r\nLessons they shared are: Follow your passion; Plan every day clearly; Belief in ourselves; Gain hands own experience; Manage your energy; Build great team; Plan for your capital; Learn from the complaint and Be god-fearing:\r\n\r\nMs. Zeanath Ashraf a social worker with Mother Theresa Touch shared the transformation of\r\nGunda Attani Aneesh into a family man and the miserable life of AIDS patients. The audience listened with tears in their eyes. Students honoured the Ammas of our campus who take care of the sanitation of the premises and hospitality of the guests. They acknowledge the value of their contribution. Let\'s keep on doing with everything involvement and mindfulness. Birthday of Dr. Anu George and Ms. Lidhiya made the occasion very warm. Special appreciation to Nayana, Franklin, Jojin, Shruthi, Sreenath Sir and Ambily Miss for the effective coordination.', 'Women\'s Day Celebration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-20 04:48:24', '2019-03-20 04:48:24', '', 68, 'http://intersmart.co.in/viswajyothi/68-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
