ograms\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Publications</strong>\n\nAn evaluation of the business model of market aggregation in hospitality industry with special reference to OYO rooms\n\nAn evaluation of the burning issues of Kasturirangan report with special reference to Idukki district.\n\nA study on recent changes in Indian consumer perception about scooters\n\nMarketing management ratios - A case study based on Jive products\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Faculty Development Programs Attended</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Attended one-day seminar on Emerging Global economic and Business Trend 26<sup>th</sup><sup>  </sup>March 2018.</li>\n 	<li>Attended a FDP on rethinking marketing on a connected world on 12<sup>th</sup><sup>  </sup>February 2016</li>\n 	<li>Attended a workshop on paradigm shift in field of CSR on 11<sup>th</sup><sup>  </sup>January 2017</li>\n 	<li>Attended International conference in the Emerging trends in market and marketing 19<sup>th</sup> and 20<sup>th</sup> February 2016</li>\n 	<li>Attended a entrepreneurship training program on 31<sup>st</sup><sup>  </sup>July 2014</li>\n 	<li>Attended a national conference on emerging vistas of management and Engineering on 24<sup>th</sup> and 25<sup>th</sup> November 2014</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Professional Society Memberships</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Member KMA</li>\n 	<li>Lions Club</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;', 'Mr. Midhun Jose', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '678-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-04-02 06:02:02', '2019-04-02 06:02:02', '', 678, 'http://www.vjcetmba.in/678-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1218, 3, '2019-04-02 06:13:10', '2019-04-02 06:13:10', '<strong>Email-ID: cyriacjoseph@vjcet.org</strong>\n\nDr. Cyriac Joseph completed his graduate studies in Economics from St. Thomas College Pala and completed M.A in Economics from Kuriakose Elias College Mannanam. Subsequently he completed M. Phil in Economics from University of Kerala. He has been selected for Teacher Fellowship under the FIP deputation Scheme of UGC Xth Plan for a period of two and a half years to complete his PhD and secured the same from Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam. He secured MBA (Marketing) from Madurai Kamaraj University and MSc (Applied Psychology) from Bharathiar University, Coimbatore. Also he has certified in Counselling Psychology from Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam Kerala. Dr. Cyriac Joseph has been the recipient of “Vidya Ratan Award” for individual contribution towards education and health by The Economics for Health and Educational Growth, New Delhi in 2012.  He has been recognized as research guide in Economics in Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam, Bharathiyar University Coimbatore and Karpakam University, Coimbatore. He has published several research articles in peer refereed journals of repute and presented research papers in several National and International seminars.\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>Educational Qualification </strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Ph.D in Economics, Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam, Kerala, (2008):</li>\n 	<li>MPhil in Economics: University of Kerala, (1994)</li>\n 	<li>M.A in Economics: University of Kerala, (1984)</li>\n 	<li>MBA (Marketing): Madurai Kamaraj University Madurai, (2010)</li>\n 	<li>M Sc Applied Psychology<em>: </em>Bharathiar University, Coimbatore, (2012)</li>\n 	<li>Certificate Course in Counseling Psychology: Department of Lifelong Learning and Extension, Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam, Keraka (2016)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Work Experience</strong></h4>\n<strong>Research </strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>1994-1995: MPhil Research Scholar, S D College Alappuzha, University of Kerala, Trivandrum.</li>\n 	<li>2015- 2018 PhD Research Scholar, Gandhian Thought and Development Studies, Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam.</li>\n 	<li>Completed Three Minor Research Projects funded by University Grants Commission.</li>\n 	<li>Recognized as research guide in Economics in Mahatma Gandhi University, Kottayam, Bharathiyar University Coimbatore and Karpakam University, Coimbatore. At present seven scholars are doing PhD.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong> </strong><strong>Teaching </strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Retired from Kuriakose Elias College Mannanam as the Head of the Research and Post Graduate Department of Economics after 32 years of teaching experience in Pre Degree, BA and MA, (1985-2017)</li>\n 	<li>Vice Principal, Marian International Institute of Management, Kuttikanam (2017-2018)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Areas of Interest </strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Formal Demography</li>\n 	<li>Population and Development</li>\n 	<li>Development Economics</li>\n 	<li>International Business</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Awards And Honours </strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>“Vidya Ratan Award” </strong>for individual contribution towards education and health by The Economics for Health and Educational Growth, New Delhi, 2012.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Publications</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li><em>“Age at Marriage as a Determinant of fertility: Nuptiality in Kerala, Trends and Differentials”</em>, Research Digest, Vol 1, Issue 3, January-March, 2007, pp14-20.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Role of Female Education on Fertility-An Examination of Kerala Experience,</em> Research Digest, Vol 1, Issue 4, April-June, 2007, pp12-16.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Impact of Demographic Transition on Older Age Groups in Kerala – The Need for Social Security”</em>, Ripples, Vol.1, Issue 2, March-August, 2007, pp 20-27.</li>\n 	<li><em>“An Analysis of District Level Fertility Differentials in Kerala”</em> in T.M George (eds) Demographic Changes and Challenges to Development, Nirmala Academic and Research Publications, Nirmala College Muvatupuzha, March 2008, pp, 90-108.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Contraceptive Prevalence in India, Evidence from NFHS – III”</em>, Research Digest, Vol 2, Issue 1, April-September, 2008, pp, 7-12.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Spatial Variations in Fertility in the State of Kerala: The Role of Religion”,</em> Research Digest, Vol 3.4 Issue 4, October-December, 2008, pp, 46-54.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Knowledge and Prevalence of HIV/AIDS”, </em>Journal of Extension and Research, Vol. XII, No. 1, July 2009, pp50-53.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Nature and Extent of Domestic Violence in India” , </em>Research Scholar, Vol.I No.II-A December 2011, pp 81-87</li>\n 	<li><em>“Population Trends in Kerala”</em>, Aureole, St’ Joseph’s Journal of Multidisciplinary Studies and Research, Vol. II &amp; III, December 2011, pp 75-86.</li>\n 	<li><em>Knowledge and Prevalence of HIV/AIDS in India”, </em>New Numbers and Letters, Vol 1, No. 1, December 2010,pp 95-105.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Determinants Of Fertility Differentials Among The Religious Groups In Kerala”</em> New Numbers and Letters, Vol 2, No. 1, December 2011,pp 51-64.</li>\n 	<li><em>Domestic Violence Against Women in India, </em>New Numbers and Letters, Vol 3, No. 1, December 2012, pp.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Satisfaction Levels of Customers Towards the Products of Malanadu Development Society”</em> New Numbers and Letters, Vol 4, No. 1, December 2013, pp. 83-85</li>\n 	<li><em>“Attitude Towards Family Size And Contraception Among The Indian Youth”,</em> New Numbers and Letters, Vol 5, No. 1, December 2014, pp.17-22</li>\n 	<li><em>“Cross Sectional Study of Female Workforce Participation And Fertility In Kerala”, </em>New Numbers and Letters, Vol 6, No. 1, December 2015, pp.230-236.</li>\n 	<li><em>“Customer’s Behaviour Towards Life Insurance Companies With Special Reference to Women Policy Holders in Alappuzha District” </em>UGC Jr. No.: 45308 Impact Factor: 1.14 | SJIF 2016:3.343 | SJIF 2017: 4.253 | ISI 2017-2018: 0673, PP 129-135</li>\n 	<li><em>Demographic Transition and the changing pattern of women work participation in Kerala, </em>Bscan, A Biannual Research Journal of Management and Socio-economic Transformation, Vol III No. 1 January 2018, PP 30-38</li>\n 	<li><em>Hazardus Effects of E-Waste: Its Generation, Management and Policy for Sustainable Development,</em> Bscan, A Biannual Research Journal of Management and Socio-economic Transformation, Vol III No. 1 January 2018, PP58-69</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Presentation of Papers in National Seminars</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Presented a paper,<em> “Impact of Demographic Transition on Older Age Groups in Kerala – The Need for Social Security”</em> in Two Day National Seminar on <em>“Globilisation, Growth and Social Security</em>”, held at St’ Aloysius College, Elthuruthu, Trissur, on 1-2- December, 2004.</li>\n 	<li>Presented a paper, <em>“An Analysis of District Level Fertility Differentials in Kerala” </em>in Two Day National Seminar on <em>“The Implication of Demographic Transition: Theoretical and Empirical Evidence”</em>, Conducted by the P-G Department of Economics, Nirmala College Muvattupuzha, on 1-2 December 2006.</li>\n 	<li>Presented a paper on <em>“Mental Health Care Expenditure in India”, </em>in Two Day National Seminar on Many Faces of Gender Inequality: Challenges to Indian Economy and society, Organised by Research and Post Graduate Department of Economics, B K College Amalagiry on 25<sup>th</sup> and 26<sup>th</sup> September 2014.</li>\n 	<li>Presented a paper in Two Day “Conference on American Studies”, organized by St’ Thomas College Pala, in association with U S Consulate General, Chennai, on 27th &amp; 28<sup>th </sup> July 2011.</li>\n 	<li>Presented a paper in Two Day Workshop on “Research Methodology and Data Anaalysis (SPSS)”, organised by the Post Graduate Department of Economics, K E College, Mannanam, on 8<sup>th</sup> and 9<sup>th</sup> December 2011.</li>\n 	<li>Presented a pape