(1219, 3, '2019-04-02 06:18:17', '2019-04-02 06:18:17', '<strong> </strong><strong>Email-ID: nelson@vjcet.org</strong>\n\nNelson Mathew is a graduate in commerce from M.G University, Kottayam and completed graduation from Deva Matha College, Kurvilangadu. He completed his MBA from Sri Krishna college of engineering and technology, Coimbatiore affiliated to Anna University Chennai. His area of specialization is Marketing and Human Resources. He has also done his Post graduate diploma in Brand Management from ICFAI University, Tripura.\n\nHis area of Interest is Training and Development and he is closely working with the corporate for the placement of MBA students. He is also training students in the area of Insurance, Banking, Mutual funds and stock markets as much of his experience is from the Industry he has worked.\n<h4><strong>Educational Qualification</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Post Graduate Diploma in Brand Management (PGDBM) from ICFAI University, Tripura.</li>\n 	<li>MBA (HR &amp; Marketing) from Sri Krishna College Of Engineering and Technology, Coimbatore.</li>\n 	<li>Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) from Deva Matha College, Kuravilangadu.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Certifications </strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong> </strong>Licentiate Certified – Insurance Institute of India</li>\n 	<li>AMFI Certified - NISM</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Work Experience</strong></h4>\n<strong>Academics</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>2011 – 13  Vel Tech College of Arts and Science , Avadi , Chennai</li>\n 	<li>2013 – 18 Marian International Institute of Management, Kuttikkanam, Idukki</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Industry</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li> Worked in various companies in Insurance sector – ICICI Prudential Life Insurance Company, Tata Aig Life Insurance and ING Life as Assistant Training Manager for a period of 5 years</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Areas of Interest </strong></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Marketing Management &amp; Brand Management</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Publications</strong></h4>\n<ol>\n 	<li>“Inclusive Innovation &amp; Sustainable Growth : The Millennium challenges” held in Rajagiri college of social sciences, kochi on 30th &amp; 31st Aug 2013. ISSN O972-9968 ” ambush marketing: an attack from the hidden position” published in Rajagiri Management Journal</li>\n 	<li>” social Marketing: role of academics, government, Public sector and NGO” held in INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT IN KERALA, university of kerala. on 14 th March 2014.ISSN 0974-6749 “role of save a family plan (NGO) in social marketing” published in Management Innovator</li>\n 	<li>” Management Perspectives : emerging Economic Models and Market structures for Inclusive growth” on 24th -25th April 2014 organized by Amity Business school at amity university Rajasthan, Jaipur ,India ISBN 978-81-929057-1-6 “CORPORATE GOVERNANCE AND CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY” published in Management Perspectives 2014</li>\n</ol>\n<h4><strong>National conference Paper Presented</strong></h4>\n“Inclusive Innovation &amp; Sustainable Growth: The Millennium challenges” held in Rajagiri college of social sciences, kochi on 30th &amp; 31st Aug 2013  presented my paper ON THE TOPIC : ” ambush marketing : an attack from the hidden position”\n\n” social Marketing: role of academics, government, Public sector and NGO” held in INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT IN KERALA, university of kerala. On 14 th March 2014. Presented my paper ON THE TOPIC : ” role of save a family plan(NGO) in social marketing”\n\n“Unleashing Ingenious Management Potential for Business endurance”  held on 9th &amp; 10th jan 2014 at Berchmans Institute of Management studies , SB COLLEGE  presented my paper on topic -” rural marketing- strategies adopted  companies”\n\n” Rejuvenating Management strategies for emerging markets” held on Jan 23rd &amp;24th 2014 at St Joseph’s college of engineering and technology presented my paper on the topic - Show rooming- an attack on the retailer”\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>International conference paper presented:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n1) International conference on India’s external sector: challenges and strategies, organized by kochi business school on 5th &amp; 6th deb 2014\n\nPresented my paper on “a study on surrogate advertisement and its pros and cons for company- a conceptual study”.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n2) International conference Management perspectives 2014″ Emerging economic models and market structures for inclusive growth” held on 24th April -25th April 2014 organized by amity business school at Amity University Rajasthan Jaipur India\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Mr. Nelson Mathew', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '683-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-04-02 06:18:17', '2019-04-02 06:18:17', '', 683, 'http://www.vjcetmba.in/683-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
